commText: Welcome back. Gaikwad and Ravindra walk out to open. RR have their impact player - Burger in, Jurel out. Boult to start off. A wide slip in.
Tushar Deshpande's bowling in IPL 2024 \nIn Chennai: 6 inns, 11 wkts, 8.72 ER \nOther venues: 6 inns, 5 wkts, 8.31 ER
Tushar Deshpande in death overs (17-20) in IPL 2024 Overs: 11 Wkts: 7 Avg: 15.42 SR: 9.4 ER: 9.81
Lowest 1st innings total in IPL 2024 89 - GT vs DC, Ahmedabad 125/9 - MI vs RR, Wankhede 137/9 - KKR vs CSK, Chennai 141/5 - RR vs CSK, Chennai
Pace vs spin in RR innings \nSpin: 0/52 in 8 overs (ER 6.50) \nPace: 5/88 in 12 overs (ER 7.33)
RR innings progression Overs 1-6: 42/0 (RR: 7.00) Overs 7-15: 52/3 (RR: 5.77) Overs 16-20: 47/2 (RR: 9.40)

Simarjeet Singh: It was difficult to bowl in this heat. Was prepared for it though. The ball is sticking into the surface, so I tried to drag the length back. Not sure what the plan is, but hope our batters play well. Easy target if we bat sensibly.

17:11 Local Time, 11:41 GMT, 17:11 IST: On a slow, turgid pitch, RR have ambled to 141. Right from the start, it looked tough going and CSK never allowed RR to get away. The openers added 42 in the powerplay but got out soon after. Parag and Samson stitched a stand but the RR skipper never looked at ease. Only the introduction of Jurel added some momentum into the innings but still the fours and sixes did not come as often as RR would have liked. Simarjeet was the pick with a three-fer as he used all his variations. It's not easy to time the ball on this so RR will feel they still are in this. Interesting chase coming up. Back for it in 5 minutes...

Tushar Deshpande to Riyan Parag, 1 run, full outside off, Riyan Parag kneels low to drive, thick inside-edge goes to the vacant mid-wicket but Tushar Deshpande gets across and cuts it off with a slide, keeps it to just one

Tushar Deshpande to Riyan Parag, SIX, pure power this. A slower short of length delivery outside off, flat-batted over long-off, need so much muscle to generate power and Riyan Parag certainly has enough
Tushar Deshpande to Riyan Parag, 2 runs, full outside off, Riyan Parag lofts straight down the ground, Gaikwad keeps it to two
Tushar Deshpande to Ashwin, 1 run, slower ball on a good length outside off, carved to deep backward point and there's no hat-trick. Was in the air though
Ravichandran Ashwin, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Tushar Deshpande to Shubham Dubey, out Caught by Shivam Dube!! Dubey caught by Dube! Two in two for Tushar Deshpande. A slower back of a length delivery outside off, Shubham Dubey is totally deceived and just hangs the bat, it lobs to backward point where Dube takes the easiest of catches. On a hat-trick now. Shubham Dubey c Shivam Dube b Tushar Deshpande 0(1)
Tushar Deshpande to Shubham Dubey, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Shubham Dubey, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Tushar Deshpande to Dhruv Jurel, out Caught by Thakur!! Full outside off, Dhruv Jurel gets under the loft and skies it. Thakur at cover settles under it and takes it. Dhruv Jurel c Thakur b Tushar Deshpande 28(18) [4s-1 6s-2]
Tushar Deshpande to Dhruv Jurel, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, seam-up short of length delivery outside off, pulled with no timing to long-on
Thakur to Riyan Parag, 1 run, full seam-up outside off, Riyan Parag drives wide of long-on and Rizvi gets across and cuts it off
Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter on a good length outside off, Dhruv Jurel cuts to sweeper cover
Thakur to Riyan Parag, 1 run, a low full-toss outside off, Riyan Parag slogs and it's a thick inside-edge to deep square leg
Thakur to Riyan Parag, 2 runs, Rizvi gets there from long-on but drops it. A slower short ball outside off, Riyan Parag can only miscue the pull, Rizvi runs a long way but can't hang on
Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, wide of the crease and slower ball full outside off, Dhruv Jurel drives and it's a thick inside-edge to short fine-leg
Shardul Thakur [3.0-0-25-0] is back into the attack
Tushar Deshpande to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, slower ball on a length and angling away from Dhruv Jurel outside off, cut to sweeper cover
Tushar Deshpande to Riyan Parag, leg byes, 1 run, Riyan Parag shuffles across well outside off as he knows the line will be there, misses the scoop and takes the legbye
Tushar Deshpande to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, very full outside off, driven to sweeper cover
Tushar Deshpande to Dhruv Jurel, SIX, Dhruv Jurel has come out and sparked momentum into the innings. A low full-toss outside off, he has slammed it over wide long-on, stand and deliver
Tushar Deshpande to Riyan Parag, 1 run, yorker length just outside off, Riyan Parag slogs and it's a thick inside-edge down to the long-on and deep mid-wicket area
Tushar Deshpande to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, Tushar Deshpande round the wicket and it's a low full-toss outside off, driven with no timing to long-on
Tushar Deshpande [2.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack
Simarjeet Singh to Riyan Parag, no run, dug in short outside off, Riyan Parag slashes and misses. End of Simarjeet Singh who has been excellent today
Simarjeet Singh to Riyan Parag, wide, this slower short ball is a tad too high as Riyan Parag lets it go, wide called
Simarjeet Singh to Riyan Parag, no run, short of length and zippy, angling into Riyan Parag who pulls and misses, beaten for pace
Simarjeet Singh to Riyan Parag, no run, full and angling into off and middle, Riyan Parag heaves but it's a thick inside-edge onto the pads, the ball rolls near his feet

Simarjeet Singh to Riyan Parag, FOUR, again a slower short ball outside off, Riyan Parag stands and belts the pull, Jadeja runs and dives with outstretched hands but it just eludes them. Full marks for the effort though
Simarjeet Singh to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, off-pace full delivery outside off, Dhruv Jurel gets forward to drive to sweeper cover
Simarjeet Singh to Dhruv Jurel, FOUR, the yorker length delivery is just outside the leg-stump, Dhruv Jurel flicks wide of deep backward square leg and it flies away, again great timing
Thakur to Riyan Parag, no run, that's wild. A back of a length delivery outside off, Riyan Parag wants to go leg-side and does not connect
Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, short of length just outside off, Dhruv Jurel works through the vacant mid-wicket area
Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, no run, full outswinger outside off, hint of movement away, Dhruv Jurel drives and is beaten, flies to Dhoni
Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, SIX, nothing edgy about this. A half-volley on the stumps, Dhruv Jurel gets slightly inside the line, flicks and what timing, flies over deep mid-wicket
Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, 2 runs, the attempted yorker is a low full-toss on the stumps, Dhruv Jurel flicks and it's a thick leading-edge that loops just wide of mid-off running to his right
Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, no run, tight good length delivery just outside off, Dhruv Jurel pushes it back
Shardul Thakur [2.0-0-16-0] is back into the attack

Highlights (Overs 7-15): - Simarjeet forces a mishit off Jaiswal and troubles Samson on arrival - Jadeja builds pressure on Buttler - Simarjeet gets Buttler, excellent catch by Deshpande - Parag hits a six to release some pressure - Theekshana bowls a tight 5-run over - Parag smacks Jadeja for a six in a 10-run over - the best in last 10 overs - Simarjeet gets Samson - records his career best in IPL
Simarjeet Singh to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, Dhruv Jurel punches to sweeper cover
Simarjeet Singh to Dhruv Jurel, no run, dug in short on the stumps, Dhruv Jurel ducks to leave
Simarjeet Singh to Riyan Parag, 1 run, slower ball dug in short outside off, pulled to deep mid-wicket
Simarjeet Singh to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, full outside off, pushed to mid-off and it's a quick single even as Gaikwad fails to pick it cleanly

486 runs by Sanju Samson in this season is the most runs for him in an IPL season (484 runs in IPL 2021) and his average (69.4) and strike-rate (158.8) this year already the best for him in a single season.
Dhruv Jurel, right handed bat, comes to the crease

It's the timeout too. CSK and Simarjeet Singh with a crucial wicket. The partnership was set and they were trying to break loose. Still 150-160 is a good score on this. It will only get slower from here.

Simarjeet Singh to Samson, out Caught by Gaikwad!! Straight to mid-off. Full seam-up delivery outside off, Samson lofts but does not get the elevation and holes out. Wanted to break the shackles but the bat turned on impact and skewed all timing. Simarjeet Singh punches the air as he roars. Samson c Gaikwad b Simarjeet Singh 15(19)
Simarjeet Singh to Samson, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Simarjeet Singh to Riyan Parag, 1 run, slower ball full outside off, Riyan Parag throws the bat on the drive, the thick outside-edge goes to third man
Simarjeet Singh to Riyan Parag, wide, dug in short outside off, left alone and it's too short, so called a wide
Simarjeet Singh [2.0-0-11-2] is back into the attack
Jadeja to Samson, 2 runs, full outside off, Samson gets forward to drive wide of extra-cover and places it wide of sweeper cover too, easy two
Jadeja to Samson, no run, flat back of a length outside off, cut again to backward point, twice in two balls
Jadeja to Samson, no run, length delivery outside off, Samson cuts but finds Simarjeet at backward point
Jadeja to Riyan Parag, 1 run, fullish just outside off, Riyan Parag taps wide of point for one, sensible batting
Jadeja to Riyan Parag, SIX, there comes the big shot. A flat fullish delivery on off and middle, Riyan Parag goes low and slogsweeps flat over deep mid-wicket
Jadeja to Samson, 1 run, fired in on a good length on middle, Samson makes room and pushes to long-off
Theekshana to Riyan Parag, no run, 104.1kph, another yorker outside off, Riyan Parag gets beaten again. Been more than 4 years since the last boundary was scored
Theekshana to Riyan Parag, no run, yorker length ball outside off, fires it outside off at 108 kph, Riyan Parag can't squeeze it out
Theekshana to Samson, 1 run, carrom ball on leg, Samson drives it along the floor to long-on
Theekshana to Riyan Parag, 1 run, pushed through on a fuller length, Riyan Parag drives it to cover for a single
Theekshana to Riyan Parag, 2 runs, darted on middle, Riyan Parag works it through square leg for a couple of runs, played with soft hands
Theekshana to Samson, 1 run, full and straight on off, Samson drives it along the carpet to long-off for a single
Maheesh Theekshana [3.0-0-23-0] is back into the attack
Jadeja to Samson, 1 run, excellent over by Jadeja. If only that catch had been taken! On a length around off and Samson lofts it over the infield at cover for a single, on the bounce to Theekshana

Jadeja to Riyan Parag, 1 run, dropped by Theekshana at deep point! Riyan Parag goes for a reverse sweep and miscues it towards the off-side, but the fielder in the deep makes a mess of it. Ran towards his left, got his hands to it but spilled it
Thakur to Riyan Parag, 1 run, pitched up by the bowler, Riyan Parag nudges it through mid-wicket for a single
Thakur to Samson, 1 run, goes for a pull against the short ball, but the timing wasn't great, just a single through mid-wicket
Thakur to Riyan Parag, 1 run, nudged to long-on by Riyan Parag for a single
Thakur to Samson, 1 run, short of a length outside off, Samson cuts it through backward point
Thakur to Riyan Parag, 1 run, pitched up by the bowler on middle and leg, Riyan Parag works it through mid-wicket for a single
Thakur to Riyan Parag, 2 runs, on a length around middle and leg, nudged through the leg-side by Riyan Parag for a couple of runs
Shardul Thakur [1.0-0-9-0] is back into the attack
Jadeja to Riyan Parag, 1 run, darted on off, Riyan Parag knocks it to the off-side for a single
Jadeja to Samson, 1 run, touch fuller on off, Samson drives it along the carpet to long-off for a single
Jadeja to Samson, no run, quicker delivery on off, Samson defends it back to Jadeja
Jadeja to Riyan Parag, 1 run, fired at the stumps, punched to mid-off with soft hands for a single
Jadeja to Samson, 1 run, full and straight on off, driven along the carpet to long-off

Jos Buttler vs Simarjeet Singh 1 run 5 balls 2 dismissals

Simarjeet Singh to Buttler, out Caught by Tushar Deshpande!! Simarjeet Singh gets another wicket. He has gotten rid of both the RR openers. This was touch full and Buttler attempted the scoop shot. Miscues it towards fine leg where Tushar completes a good running catch. Simarjeet Singh is pumped up, his celebration says it all. Buttler c Tushar Deshpande b Simarjeet Singh 21(25) [4s-2]
Simarjeet Singh to Buttler, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Jadeja to Buttler, 1 run, tossed up delivery around off, Buttler pushes it into the off-side for a single

Simarjeet Singh to Jaiswal, out Caught by Gaikwad!! Short and quick on off, Jaiswal goes for a pull but loses shape. Gets a top edge towards cover and Gaikwad charges in to complete a safe catch. Jaiswal walks back after playing a cameo. The first over after powerplay results in a wicket. Jaiswal c Gaikwad b Simarjeet Singh 24(21) [4s-3 6s-1]
Simarjeet Singh to Jaiswal, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Only the third time in 12 matches both RR openers have survived the powerplay.
Least sixes hit in powerplay in IPL 2024 15 - CSK 16 - RR* 16 - GT 19 - PBKS 21 - LSG - All other five teams have hit more than 30 sixes in the Powerplay phase this year.
Least wickets picked in Powerplay in IPL 2024 14 - PBKS 15 - CSK* 17 - RCB 19 - LSG 19 - DC

Timeout! RR openers are off to a watchful start. The pitch isn't that great for batting as the ball is sticking into the surface. Would be interesting to see how they play against spinners after the powerplay..

Highlights (Overs 1-6) - Deshpande starts with a tight over - Theekshana shares the new-ball - Buttler gets going with a boundary - Gaikwad misses a chance to run Buttler out - Jaiswal breaks the shackles with a six - Jaiswal hits consecutive fours off Thakur - RR take 42 off the powerplay
Theekshana to Buttler, FOUR, low full toss on middle and leg, Buttler sweeps it over square leg for a boundary. A productive powerplay for the Royals
Theekshana to Buttler, no run, quicker through the air, punched to cover by Buttler

Thakur to Jaiswal, FOUR, back-to-back boundaries. Pitched up by the bowler outside off, Jaiswal throws his hands it and thumps it over point for four runs

"Dhoni asked for, what looks like, a lower-back brace in between overs," informs Kaushik from the Chepauk..

Jaiswal and Buttler are at the crease. Jaiswal is on strike. Tushar Deshpande will open the attack
